Reasoning: The paper deals with complexity theory and the characterization of type-two polynomial-time computability. This falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also discusses oracle machines and their interactions, which is related to data structures (cs.DS). The use of regular polynomials and the restriction on lookahead revisions may also be of interest to researchers in logic and computation (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper deals with the closure properties of certain classes of feasible functionals, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.TCS).
